          <h3 class="mb-pillar-title">Free Diagnostics First</h3>
          <p class="mb-pillar-body">MacBook repairs can be complex and expensive — we never start work without giving you a full diagnostic report and upfront quote. If the repair cost approaches your MacBook's current value, we'll tell you honestly and help you explore alternatives including data recovery or trade-in options.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-pillar-card">
          <div class="mb-pillar-icon-wrapper">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/><polyline points="9 12 11 14 15 10"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-pillar-title">Warranty on Every Repair</h3>
          <p class="mb-pillar-body">Screen repairs carry a 30-day to lifetime warranty depending on part tier. Battery replacements include a 90-day warranty. All other repairs carry a lifetime warranty on parts and labour — so your MacBook stays working long after it leaves our shop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-pillar-card">
          <div class="mb-pillar-icon-wrapper">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 01-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-pillar-title">Your Data Stays Safe</h3>
          <p class="mb-pillar-body">We take data security seriously — your files remain untouched during hardware repairs. For liquid damage or data recovery cases, we document the device state on arrival and walk you through the recovery process step by step so you know exactly what's happening with your data.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-cost-section" id="pricing">
    <div class="mb-container">
      <div class="mb-section-header">
        <h2 class="mb-section-title">Worried About Repair Cost? You Have Options.</h2>
        <p class="mb-section-subtitle">Most customers use one of these options to lower their repair cost.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mb-cost-grid">
        <div class="mb-cost-card">
          <div class="mb-cost-icon-wrapper">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" x2="12" y1="1" y2="23"/><path d="M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-cost-title">We'll Match Any Local Repair Price</h3>
          <p class="mb-cost-body">Found a lower price at another Winnipeg repair shop? We'll match it — so you don't overpay. No pressure. No hassle.</p>
          <a href="sms:2045009757?body=Hey%20Mobile%20Tech%20Lab!%20I%20want%20a%20better%20price%20on%20a%20repair!" class="mb-price-match-btn">
            Check If We Can Match Your Price
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-cost-card">
          <div class="mb-cost-icon-wrapper">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="M3 12a9 9 0 1 0 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 0-6.74 2.74L3 8"/><path d="M3 3v5h5"/><path d="M12 7v5l4 2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="mb-cost-title">Lower Your MacBook Repair Cost With a Trade-In</h3>
          <p class="mb-cost-body">Trade in phones, tablets, consoles, or laptops — even broken ones — to reduce today's repair cost.</p>
          <p class="mb-cost-note">Get paid via Cash, E-Transfer, or Store Credit</p>
          <a href="/trade-in" class="mb-trade-in-btn">
            Lower My MacBook Repair Cost &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mb-pricing-context">
        <p class="mb-context-paragraph">MacBook repair costs are primarily driven by the display and logic board. A MacBook Air M2 screen replacement is significantly more expensive than an Intel MacBook Air due to the newer panel technology and tighter integration with the chassis. <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-ca/102894" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mb-context-link">Apple's battery service documentation</a> explains when battery replacement is recommended based on cycle count and maximum capacity percentage.</p>
        <p class="mb-context-paragraph">Many customers are surprised that a MacBook Pro display replacement can approach or exceed the cost of a refurbished MacBook — particularly on M-chip Pro and Max models with Liquid Retina XDR displays. <a href="https://www.ifixit.com/Search?query=macbook+teardown" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="mb-context-link">iFixit's MacBook teardowns</a> illustrate exactly why these repairs are complex, showing how tightly the display, battery, and logic board components are integrated.</p>
        <p class="mb-context-paragraph">If the repair cost approaches your MacBook's current market value, we'll always tell you clearly and walk you through your options — including data recovery and transfer to a new machine, or trade-in value toward a replacement device from our pre-owned inventory.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

